<item>
            <title>[FELIX-897] Empty system package is exported when a semicolon is present in &quot;extra&quot; configuration</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-897</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Felix exports an empty system package when the felix &quot;extra&quot; configuration property starts with a semicolon.&lt;br/&gt;
For instance, with the following configuration &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;org.osgi.framework.system.packages.extra=${jre-${java.specification.version}}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;jre-1.5=; \&lt;br/&gt;
 com.sun.accessibility.internal.resources; \&lt;br/&gt;
 com.sun.beans; \&lt;br/&gt;
 ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then, Felix interprets the semicolon (the one after &quot;jre-1.5=&quot;) as an empty system package, which is exported to other bundles.&lt;br/&gt;
This may lead to tricky issues, especially for bundles using &quot;DynamicImport-Package: *&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For instance, the following code returns null, when getting a resource from the bundle archive (and when there is &lt;br/&gt;
&quot;DynamicImport-Package: *&quot; in the manifest):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  InputStream in = getClass().getClassLoader().getResourceAsStream(&quot;MyResource.properties&quot;);&lt;/p&gt;</description>
